reviewText: All four films are first class with fine production values. The films are in their original formats (widescreen). All supplements that were on the individual discs, are there.

This is a great set of Westerns from 1954 to 1972. This is a 4 DVD set with three out of four disks that are double-sided. All movies are in Widescreen and a few have the ability to watch in full screen. The subtitles vary from each movie, but are; English SDH and Spanish.

"The Comancheros" (1961/color/107min/Widescreen)
-John Wayne,Stuart Whitman, Ina Balin, Lee Marvin; Directed by Michael Curtiz
"The Last Wagon" (1956/color/98min/Widescreen&Full screen)
-Richard Widmark, Felicia Farr, Susan Kohner, Tommy Rettig; Directed by Delmer Davis
"The Culpepper Cattle Co." (1972/color/92min/Widescreen&Full screen)
-Gary Grimes, Billy "Green" Bush, Luke Askew; Directed by Dick Richards
"Broken Lance" (1954/color/96min/Widescreen&Full screen)
-Robert Wagner, Jean Peters, Richard Widmark, Katy Jurado, Eduardo Franz; Directed by Edward Dmytryk

Overall this is a great collection of westerns and I would recommend this.
Been looking for "Last Wagon" for year>
You will love this movie!!!!  I did!!!
Some hard to find great westerns.
